WEBVTT

00:00.867 --> 00:07.272
♪♪

00:07.274 --> 00:10.008
Joe: Nothing makes
students go wild

00:10.010 --> 00:11.876
Like when a teacher says,

00:11.878 --> 00:14.746
"today, we will
be watching a movie."

00:14.748 --> 00:16.281
They go nuts.

00:16.283 --> 00:18.082
Yell and stuff.

00:18.084 --> 00:19.884
And as an educator,

00:19.886 --> 00:21.886
I try not to take it personally

00:21.888 --> 00:24.823
Because movies are pretty good.

00:24.825 --> 00:27.359
Have you seen "spirited away"?

00:27.361 --> 00:30.095
I know the alternative
is learning.

00:30.097 --> 00:31.696
But at the same time,

00:31.698 --> 00:34.767
I think the students
are probably more excited

00:34.769 --> 00:35.968
Than they should be

00:35.970 --> 00:38.903
Because classroom
movie experiences

00:38.905 --> 00:41.105
Are only just okay.

00:41.107 --> 00:43.976
The school library has
a limited selection,

00:43.978 --> 00:47.646
And they often end up
watching films such as...

00:47.648 --> 00:49.848
"fresh water story,"

00:49.850 --> 00:53.251
"julius caesar revealed,"

00:53.253 --> 00:56.455
"the great flying day,"

00:56.457 --> 00:59.391
"tales by old pheasant,"

00:59.393 --> 01:01.860
"the patriot man,"

01:01.862 --> 01:05.063
"trash can cats
go rom-pomp-pomp,"

01:05.065 --> 01:08.600
Or "the day after tomorrow."

01:08.602 --> 01:10.202
For the past five years, though,

01:10.204 --> 01:13.271
I usually end up
showing my favorite,

01:13.273 --> 01:15.273
"the adventures of otto."

01:15.275 --> 01:26.418
♪♪

01:26.420 --> 01:28.821
I haven't seen a man
who looks like that,

01:28.823 --> 01:30.355
But if he stole a book
from the library

01:30.357 --> 01:32.290
I'm down to help
you find him.

01:32.292 --> 01:33.892
Joe: Ha!

01:33.894 --> 01:36.028
I could watch this one
over and over,

01:36.030 --> 01:39.564
But my students
have gotten tired of it.

01:39.566 --> 01:41.566
Humor changes.

01:41.568 --> 01:42.501
Hello.

01:42.503 --> 01:44.436
My name is joe pera,

01:44.438 --> 01:47.239
And though movie days
are fun for students,

01:47.241 --> 01:49.508
For teachers,
they can be as stressful

01:49.510 --> 01:52.310
As landing an airplane
on a river.

01:52.312 --> 01:54.446
This Friday
is the last day of school

01:54.448 --> 01:56.114
Before winter break.

01:56.116 --> 01:58.183
And as entertainment curator,

01:58.185 --> 02:00.185
I need to pick out
something to watch

02:00.187 --> 02:02.587
That's both enjoyable
for my students.

02:02.589 --> 02:05.057
But harmless enough that
I won't get in trouble

02:05.059 --> 02:07.259
With the school or parents.

02:07.261 --> 02:12.797
♪♪

02:12.799 --> 02:14.933
Near the top of my list of fears

02:14.935 --> 02:17.202
Is getting bit on the nose
by a snake

02:17.204 --> 02:21.139
And dying with a swollen honker
in the british hospital.

02:21.141 --> 02:24.276
But above even that
is losing my job.

02:24.278 --> 02:27.946
That's why I am spending the day
prescreening options.

02:27.948 --> 02:30.749
You got to prescreen options.

02:30.751 --> 02:33.351
It's something they should
have taught a teacher school

02:33.353 --> 02:36.755
'cause last year, I learned
my lesson the hard way.

02:36.757 --> 02:40.425
Andrea had the most
behavior points this spring,

02:40.427 --> 02:43.161
So she brought in
her favorite film

02:43.163 --> 02:45.497
"wish it ain't so."

02:49.770 --> 02:53.372
[<i> bell rings,</i>
<i> indistinct conversations</i> ]

02:53.374 --> 02:55.274
Interesting.

03:05.252 --> 03:07.051
<i> Hey, you [bleep] bitches.</i>

03:07.053 --> 03:09.121
[ students laugh ]

03:13.594 --> 03:16.528
[ glass shatters ]

03:16.530 --> 03:18.997
Please don't tell your parents.

03:18.999 --> 03:21.533
Luckily, they didn't.

03:21.535 --> 03:24.469
Why would that be
the first line of anything?

03:24.471 --> 03:25.938
[ sighs ]

03:25.940 --> 03:27.406
Just wanna reward my students

03:27.408 --> 03:30.008
For a good first half
of school year

03:30.010 --> 03:33.078
By showing them
a good first half movie,

03:33.080 --> 03:34.679
I signed up to teach choir,

03:34.681 --> 03:38.683
But I'm somehow now both
a film critic and censurer,

03:38.685 --> 03:39.752
Trying to figure out

03:39.754 --> 03:42.955
Can something that
avoids violence or swearing

03:42.957 --> 03:46.158
Ever be considered great art?

03:46.160 --> 03:48.193
I don't know.

03:49.496 --> 03:52.230
You're probably now thinking.

03:52.232 --> 03:54.899
Why not just put on
the latest comedy special

03:54.901 --> 03:57.302
Of the popular ventriloquist.

03:57.304 --> 03:58.971
That would put me in danger

03:58.973 --> 04:00.705
Of getting fired, as well,

04:00.707 --> 04:02.841
For showing
the students something

04:02.843 --> 04:04.777
That could be deemed political.

04:04.779 --> 04:06.711
As you and I both know,

04:06.713 --> 04:10.715
All ventriloquist are
overtly republican.

04:10.717 --> 04:13.318
That's why I got
so nervous last month

04:13.320 --> 04:15.854
When gabriel did
his lunch performance.

04:15.856 --> 04:17.189
Long story, but, basically,

04:17.191 --> 04:19.391
We give him
the last five minutes

04:19.393 --> 04:20.725
Of lunch each month

04:20.727 --> 04:23.329
To perform
for the other students.

04:28.602 --> 04:31.403
His decision to not talk
through the puppet,

04:31.405 --> 04:34.139
But instead re-create
the title sequence

04:34.141 --> 04:35.340
Of "caddyshack"

04:35.342 --> 04:37.142
Was, to put it bluntly,

04:37.144 --> 04:40.745
A freakin' relief.

04:40.747 --> 04:44.349
After, I spoke with gabriel,
and he shared his thoughts

04:44.351 --> 04:49.021
On the connection between
conservatism and ventriloquism.

04:49.023 --> 04:51.023
It was fairly obvious
to observe,

04:51.025 --> 04:53.625
But I still haven't
figured out why.

04:53.627 --> 04:57.496
I've got theories,
but the nicest of them is,

04:57.498 --> 04:59.498
It's a throwback
to old times.

04:59.500 --> 05:01.299
In fact, ventriloquism
can even be traced

05:01.301 --> 05:03.702
Back to ancient greece,
ancient egypt,

05:03.704 --> 05:04.837
I didn't know that.

05:04.839 --> 05:07.772
But make this
thing talk?

05:07.774 --> 05:10.042
Modern ventriloquism
is the oppression of puppets.

05:10.044 --> 05:12.377
So right, my man.

05:12.379 --> 05:13.645
People are thrilled

05:13.647 --> 05:16.181
By the spectacle
of a puppet speaking,

05:16.183 --> 05:18.250
But only with
constant reassurance

05:18.252 --> 05:20.252
That it's not
actually speaking

05:20.254 --> 05:22.987
By always having a hand
up its back.

05:22.989 --> 05:25.524
It's very...
[clicks tongue]

05:25.526 --> 05:29.728
I feel this applies
to ventriloquism post-1960,

05:29.730 --> 05:32.130
When puppets were liberated
by jim henson

05:32.132 --> 05:34.266
And allowed to exist
as autonomous muppets.

05:34.268 --> 05:35.333
Hmm.

05:35.335 --> 05:37.402
If jeff dunham
and terry fator fans

05:37.404 --> 05:39.471
Saw kermit the frog
riding a bicycle,

05:39.473 --> 05:42.941
They would cry blasphemy,

05:42.943 --> 05:44.609
Then bludgeon it.

05:44.611 --> 05:46.745
'cause something
so free and beautiful

05:46.747 --> 05:50.014
Should not be
allowed to exist.

05:50.016 --> 05:51.616
Oh, and gabriel,

05:51.618 --> 05:53.418
How do you know
about "caddyshack"?

05:53.420 --> 05:55.353
Oh, it was one
of the three videos

05:55.355 --> 05:57.622
We had at
the hitobo research base.

05:57.624 --> 05:58.623
Oh.

05:58.625 --> 06:00.825
By the way,
if you're wondering

06:00.827 --> 06:04.563
If this program has an agenda,
it does --

06:04.565 --> 06:08.300
To encourage everyone
to pick up an instrument.

06:13.107 --> 06:14.973
It's not
just ventriloquist.

06:14.975 --> 06:16.775
If you think about it,

06:16.777 --> 06:18.643
Other types
of entertainment people

06:18.645 --> 06:22.046
Can also be linked to particular
political leanings.

06:22.048 --> 06:24.048
Correct me if I'm wrong,

06:24.050 --> 06:25.718
But I think that actors,
for example,

06:25.720 --> 06:27.185
Tend liberal,

06:27.187 --> 06:29.388
Except for, of course,
ronald reagan.

06:29.390 --> 06:32.257
Sports announcers, conservative.

06:32.259 --> 06:36.729
Magicians, libertarian.

06:36.731 --> 06:40.132
I was thinking about this
when sarah and I went

06:40.134 --> 06:41.333
To the evelyn bonnet

06:41.335 --> 06:43.802
In forest roberts theatre.

06:43.804 --> 06:45.137
You probably know her.

06:45.139 --> 06:49.474
She was featured last season
on "usa is gifted."

06:49.476 --> 06:50.675
Next.

06:50.677 --> 06:53.812
Joe: I'm sure you want
to wait in on this slide

06:53.814 --> 06:55.948
The show is terrific.
I want to tell her so.

06:55.950 --> 07:00.218
Oh, my god!
Yo, joe!

07:00.220 --> 07:02.687
Carlos, wow.

07:02.689 --> 07:04.689
I didn't expect
to see you.

07:04.691 --> 07:07.692
Yeah, man, I'm up here
once a month for sales meetings.

07:07.694 --> 07:10.763
I just grab a hotel room bar
hop for eight or nine hours.

07:10.765 --> 07:12.164
Okay.

07:12.166 --> 07:14.366
Enough about
my rock star life.

07:14.368 --> 07:16.034
You going to introduce me
to your sister?

07:16.036 --> 07:19.704
Actually, carlos,
this is my girlfriend, sarah.

07:19.706 --> 07:20.773
Damn!

07:20.775 --> 07:23.308
I thought the grand finale
was the last time

07:23.310 --> 07:24.909
My jaw would drop tonight.

07:24.911 --> 07:26.711
What up, sarah?

07:26.713 --> 07:28.513
It's nice to meet you,
carlos.

07:28.515 --> 07:29.782
What happened
to your arm?

07:29.784 --> 07:31.049
Nothing.

07:31.051 --> 07:32.451
Man: Next.

07:32.453 --> 07:34.586
Yeah.

07:34.588 --> 07:36.789
Weird, but, like,
interesting stuff.

07:36.791 --> 07:38.523
Thank you for coming
to the show.

07:38.525 --> 07:42.127
How did you turn that guinea pig
into a bowl of pico de gallo?

07:42.129 --> 07:44.663
A magician never
reveals her secrets.

07:44.665 --> 07:46.598
But if you're interested
in magic,

07:46.600 --> 07:50.735
I have some dvds for beginners
at the merch table.

07:50.737 --> 07:54.072
Don't ever try
to sell a salesman!

07:54.074 --> 07:57.209
Wrong!
[ laughs ]

07:57.211 --> 07:58.410
One at a time.
So good.

07:58.412 --> 08:00.745
Such a good show.
Aww, thank you.

08:00.747 --> 08:03.015
Are you a magician,
as well?

08:03.017 --> 08:04.149
Me? Oh, no.

08:04.151 --> 08:05.417
Crowds are not
my favorite,

08:05.419 --> 08:07.752
And my fingers are
bulky from climbing.

08:07.754 --> 08:09.888
That's weird because
I was picking up

08:09.890 --> 08:12.491
Some serious magician vibes
from you,

08:12.493 --> 08:14.827
And I'm usually never wrong
about vibes here.

08:14.829 --> 08:16.495
Here.

08:16.497 --> 08:18.497
Check your pocket.

08:21.101 --> 08:23.836
30% off any of my dvds
at the merch table.

08:23.838 --> 08:26.238
We need more women in stem,
and by that,

08:26.240 --> 08:27.572
I mean skateboarding,
television,

08:27.574 --> 08:28.773
E-sports, and magic.

08:28.775 --> 08:31.576
Photographer: Okay.
Big smile.

08:31.578 --> 08:34.513
Good luck.
Thank you.

08:34.515 --> 08:36.048
Hi, thanks for coming
to the show.

08:36.050 --> 08:40.853
It was such a great show.
I just had a quick question.

08:40.855 --> 08:42.320
I read in a magazine

08:42.322 --> 08:44.589
That penn jillette
is a libertarian,

08:44.591 --> 08:46.458
And I was wondering
if all magicians

08:46.460 --> 08:48.060
Are libertarians.

08:48.062 --> 08:49.394
I will say this.

08:49.396 --> 08:51.864
Magic, in a way,
is political freedom.

08:51.866 --> 08:53.131
I make my own rules.

08:53.133 --> 08:55.868
I'm not even governed
by the laws of reality.

08:55.870 --> 08:57.536
Cool.

08:57.538 --> 08:59.071
Do you believe in magic?

08:59.073 --> 09:00.873
Only miracles.

09:00.875 --> 09:02.140
Interesting.

09:02.142 --> 09:04.476
Is your dvd anything like
your show tonight?

09:04.478 --> 09:06.478
I kept thinking it'd be
the perfect thing

09:06.480 --> 09:08.080
For my class to watch.

09:08.082 --> 09:09.347
It definitely
would be.

09:09.349 --> 09:10.415
Okay. Photo time.

09:10.417 --> 09:12.751
3, 2, 1...

09:14.889 --> 09:16.354
$30.

09:16.356 --> 09:18.623
[ screams ]

09:18.625 --> 09:20.292
Well, bob, from arizona,

09:20.294 --> 09:23.696
Have you checked
your pockets recently?

09:23.698 --> 09:27.031
Is this your driver's license?

09:27.033 --> 09:29.301
Everyone give bob
a round of applause.

09:29.303 --> 09:31.337
You can go take a seat.

09:34.040 --> 09:36.174
So that just happened.

09:36.176 --> 09:38.376
I'd like to see god do that.

09:38.378 --> 09:40.044
We shouldn't need these things
anyways.

09:40.046 --> 09:43.648
People should be able
to drive at age 12.

09:43.650 --> 09:45.717
And what do we say about taxes,
dee dee?

09:45.719 --> 09:47.986
"uh, that's theft, bitch."

09:47.988 --> 09:49.588
[ sighs ]

09:51.325 --> 09:55.727
I guess we'll be watching
"the adventures of otto" again.

09:55.729 --> 09:59.131
[ upbeat music plays ]

09:59.133 --> 10:06.739
♪♪

10:06.741 --> 10:14.346
♪♪

